{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68fb2821-2acd-4360-a13d-580f4c93b674","content":"## `UseLegacyV2RuntimeActivationPolicy` set to 1\n\nThis setting (from `<startup>` in your app's config or the registry) changes how mixed-mode (C++/CLI) assemblies and COM components built against CLR v2 are loaded.\n\n**What it does:**\n\n- Binds CLR v2-targeting components directly into the **v4 runtime** process-wide, instead of loading CLR v2 side-by-side.\n- Mimics .NET 2.0-era \"one runtime per process\" behavior where the newest runtime always handles legacy components.\n\n**Effect on runtime selection:**\n\n| Without (default) | With (`= 1`) |\n|-|-|\n| CLR v2 components load CLR v2 side-by-side | CLR v2 components are activated against CLR v4 |\n| Multiple runtimes may coexist in-proc | Single runtime (v4) handles everything |\n\n**When you'll see this:** Loading legacy mixed-mode DLLs or COM servers that target .NET 2.0/3.5 into a .NET 4+ process.\n\n**Typical config:**\n```xml\n<configuration>\n  <startup useLegacyV2RuntimeActivationPolicy=\"true\">\n    <supportedRuntime version=\"v4.0\"/>\n  </startup>\n</configuration>\n```\n\nIf you're not intentionally hosting legacy v2 components, you can safely remove it and let the default side-by-side policy apply.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9205281d-8de6-41a9-abe5-b73be585a91e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a specific CLR (Common Language Runtime) activation log message: \"UseLegacyV2RuntimeActivationPolicy is set to 1\". They want to know what it means and how it affects runtime selection.\n\nThis is a .NET Framework question about CLR hosting and activation policy. I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase, as this is a general .NET Framework concept.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about this CLR activation policy setting.","outputTokens":477,"requestId":"5032:5409:1EDD25:268834:69F550FE"},"id":"058175f4-4225-4820-bce8-0bdffa91b740","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:19:05.261Z","parentId":"cbbd372b-924c-42fc-9768-dfb7cdca540f"}
